	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Atrocitus</h1>
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		<div id="contentSub2"></div>
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#searchInput">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><table class="infobox" style="width:22em;width: 24em; background: #f2f9ff;"><tbody><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #99c2ff;">Atrocitus</th></tr><tr><td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:Atrocitus.png" class="image"><img alt="Atrocitus.png" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/aa/Atrocitus.png" decoding="async" width="250" height="372" data-file-width="250" data-file-height="372" /></a><div>Atrocitus. Promotional cover art for <i><a href="/wiki/Final_Crisis" title="Final Crisis">Final Crisis</a>: Rage of the Red Lanterns</i> #1, by <a href="/wiki/Shane_Davis" title="Shane Davis">Shane Davis</a>.</div></td></tr><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;background: #99c2ff;">Publication information</th></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="width: 40%;"><a href="/wiki/Category:Comics_publishing_companies" title="Category:Comics publishing companies">Publisher</a></th><td><a href="/wiki/DC_Comics" title="DC Comics">DC Comics</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="width: 40%;"><a href="/wiki/First_appearance" title="First appearance">First appearance</a></th><td><b>First appearance:</b><br /><i><a href="/wiki/Green_Lantern_(comic_book)" title="Green Lantern (comic book)">Green Lantern</a></i> vol. 4 #25 (December 2007)<br /><b>Chronological first appearance:</b><br /><i>Green Lantern</i> vol. 4 #29 (May 2008)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="width: 40%;"><a href="/wiki/Category:Comics_creators" title="Category:Comics creators">Created by</a></th><td><a href="/wiki/Geoff_Johns" title="Geoff Johns">Geoff Johns</a><br /><a href="/wiki/Ethan_Van_Sciver" title="Ethan Van Sciver">Ethan Van Sciver</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;background: #99c2ff;">In-story information</th></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="width: 40%;">Alter ego</th><td>Atros</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="width: 40%;">Place of origin</th><td>Ryut</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="width: 40%;">Team affiliations</th><td><a href="/wiki/Red_Lantern_Corps" title="Red Lantern Corps">Red Lantern Corps</a><br />The Five Inversions<br />The Empire of Tears</td></tr><tr><th scope="row" style="width: 40%;">Abilities</th><td><a href="/wiki/Power_ring_(weapon)#Red" class="mw-redirect" title="Power ring (weapon)">Red Power Ring</a><br />Superhuman Strength and Durability</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p><b>Atrocitus</b> (<b>Atros</b>) is a fictional <a href="/wiki/Supervillain" title="Supervillain">supervillain</a> appearing in <a href="/wiki/American_comic_books" class="mw-redirect" title="American comic books">American comic books</a> published by <a href="/wiki/DC_Comics" title="DC Comics">DC Comics</a>. Atrocitus is an enemy to the <a href="/wiki/Guardians_of_the_Universe" title="Guardians of the Universe">Guardians of the Universe</a> and <a href="/wiki/Sinestro" title="Sinestro">Sinestro</a>, their former <a href="/wiki/Green_Lantern" title="Green Lantern">Green Lantern</a>. He is the leader of the Red Lantern Corps.
</p>
